# Comunication Protocol
*Author: Pedro Correia*
*Date:01/05/2026*
## Abstract
- Similar to class B *LoRa* protocols, a timed, synchronized gateway awakens after T_DS (time of deep sleep) together with the sensor nodes. After reading the sensor values, it controls and synchronizes them before sending them all back to sleep. If the network is available, it then forwards the data to Blynk over MQTT.
```
.----
| **Sensor Nodes**
| ┌────────┐   ┌────────┐           ┌────────┐
| │  nS,1  │   │  nS,2  │   · · ·   │  nS,N  │
| └───┬────┘   └───┬────┘           └───┬────┘
|     |            |        LoRa        |
|     '------------'--------------------'
'-----                     |
                           v
              .-------------------------.            .---------------.
              |       **Gateway**       |    MQTT    |   **Cloud**   |
              |   Decision & control    |<---------->|     Blynk     |
              '-------------------------'            '---------------'
                            |                        
.-----                      | LoRa
|            .--------------+--------------.
|            |              |              |
|            v              v              v
|         .-------.      .-------.      .-------.
|         | nL,1  |      | nL,2  |· · · | nL,N  |
|         '-------'      '-------'      '-------'
| **Light Control Nodes**
'----
```
